{"title_page": "1987\u201388 Associate Members' Cup", "text_new": "The '''1987\u201388 Associate Members' Cup''', known as the '''1987\u201388 Sherpa Van Trophy''' for sponsorship reasons, was the 5th staging of the [[Associate Members' Cup]], a knockout competition for [[English football]] clubs in the [[Football League Third Division|Third]] and [[Football League Fourth Division|Fourth]] Divisions (now known as [[Football League One|League One]] and [[Football League Two|Two]]).\n\nThe winners were [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]], who defeated [[Burnley F.C.|Burnley]] 2\u20130 in the final. This marked the only time two previous English champions have met in the final of this competition, and made Wolves the first former champions to have won the trophy, Portsmouth the only other having won the EFL trophy in 2019.\n\nThe competition began on 13 October 1987 and ended with the final on 29 May 1988.\nThe tournament begins with clubs divided into a Northern and a Southern section, and teams entering a preliminary group stage. Each section then gradually eliminates the qualifying teams in knock-out fashion until each has a winning finalist. At this point, the two winning finalists faced each other in the combined final for the honour of the trophy.\n\n== Preliminary round ==\n\n=== Northern Section ===\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n{{#invoke:sports table|main|style=WDL\n|res_col_header=Q\n|show_positions=n\n|ptsfirst=y\n|sortable_table=y\n|title=Group 1\n\n|team1=BRN|name_BRN=[[Burnley F.C.|Burnley]]\n|team2=ROC|name_ROC=[[Rochdale A.F.C.|Rochdale]]\n|team3=TRA|name_TRA=[[Tranmere Rovers F.C.|Tranmere Rovers]]\n|win_BRN=2|draw_BRN=0|loss_BRN=0|gf_BRN=5|ga_BRN=3\n|win_ROC=0|draw_ROC=1|loss_ROC=1|gf_ROC=2|ga_ROC=3\n|win_TRA=0|draw_TRA=1|loss_TRA=1|gf_TRA=1|ga_TRA=2\n\n|col_A=#ccffcc|text_A=\n|result1=A|result2=A\n|update=complete|source=\n}}\n{{OneLegStart|date=y|team-width=15em}}\n{{OneLegResult|date=Oct 13|Rochdale||0\u20130|Tranmere Rovers}}\n{{